use names fitting for attractions.
use accurate examples for Maplet's typical use.

Maplet is often referred to as "The Maplet"

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Price and Opening Hours fields
commitResults.messageBody:
Maplet has no option to include price and opening hours, which is
essential information for trip planning.

Adding these two fields will allow users to fill in more details about
attractions of interest, improving the functionalities of Maplet.

Having separate fields rather than tags will allow for easier
implementations for sorting or listing in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix tests to accomodate new fields
commitResults.messageBody:
Existing tests are buggy with the addition of new fields.

Including the new fields for the tests restore their functionality.

To maintain the reliability of existing tests.

commitResults.messageTitle: Write tests for Opening Hours and Price
commitResults.messageBody:
Opening hours and price classes are untested.

Writing tests for opening hours and price have uncovered hidden bugs
which have been fixed.

Improving code coverage, and preventing any bugs from these classes
from cascading into bigger problems down the line.

OpeningHours will throw an error if the field was empty. which is
unintended behaviour.

Supporting a "null" version of OpeningHours will fix this problem.

This implementation will allow for it to be supported for user inputs,
and will still have the functionalities such as checking if an
attraction is open at a specific time.

The regex for 24 hour time is supplemented with examples of both valid
and invalid for better readability.

The additions of comments conflicts with the
addition of opening hours and price.

Conflicts were handled, with small additions to
ensure that code still works.

This ensures the tests functionalities and code
functionalities are mantained.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change OpeningHours regex to accept variable space
commitResults.messageBody:
OpeningHours regex only accepts 0-1 spaces.

Changing this allows the regex to be more lenient.

Improves the user experience, by accepting non-problematic minor typos.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change price regex to accept decimals and units
commitResults.messageBody:
Price does not accept units or decimals, resulting in limited
functionality.

Adding currencies support, as well as decimals, allow for users to
enter more specific information into Maplet.

The regex is restricted to the 3 letter ISO code or the
currency symbol itself allows for these functionalities, but without
resulting in too much unintended behaviour.

Checkstyle errors as a result of changing code.

Rectifying errors detected by checkstyle.

In order to better stay aligned with coding standards.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG for opening hours and price
commitResults.messageBody:
UG does not include the commands format for these new fields.

Updating the UG keeps it up to date with the features.

For users to be better informed of the functionalities of the app.

Maplet's exit message mentions AddressBook, which is not the app name.

Updating the message to have Maplet instead of AddressBook.

For better naming consistency.

Opening hours supports a null version, but the parser does not.

Changing the parser functionality to accept an add command without an
opening hours field.

In order to support 24-hour attractions, which don't have an opening or
closing time.
